<p>
An example bifunctor is obtained by extending the &#x2013;&gt; to morphisms:
given <code>f : A ‚ü∂ B , g : C ‚ü∂ D</code> we define <code>(f ‚ü∂ g) : (B ‚ü∂ C) ‚Üí (A ‚ü∂ C)</code> by
<code>Œª h ‚Üí f ‚®æ h ‚®æ g</code> as this is the only way to define it so as to meet the type requirements.
</p>
